  "prompt": "Can I apply for internet banking in Andhra bank without visiting the branch?",
  "response": "Yes, you can apply for internet banking with Andhra Bank without visiting the branch, provided you meet certain criteria. Typically, if you already have a bank account and your mobile number is registered with the bank, you can usually complete the application process online. \n\nHere are the general steps you might follow:\n\n1. **Visit the Andhra Bank Official Website**: Navigate to the official Andhra Bank website.\n\n2. **Locate Internet Banking Services**: Find the section for Internet Banking. This is typically found in the services or online banking menu.\n\n3. **Registration**: If you're a new user, look for an option to register for internet banking. This may require you to enter details such as your account number, registered mobile number, and other personal information for verification.\n\n4. **Follow Instructions**: Follow the prompts to complete the registration process. You may receive an OTP (One Time Password) on your registered mobile number for verification.\n\n5. **Set Up Credentials**: After verification, you will be prompted to set up your username and password.\n\n6. **Access Your Account**: Once you've completed the registration, you should be able to log in to your internet banking account using your new credentials.\n\nIf you face any issues or if your account doesn't allow for online registration, you may need to contact customer support for assistance. Additionally, if you\u2019re a new customer and trying to open a new account, you may need to visit the branch to complete the account opening process.",
